A simple 3D scene created in Blender featuring a donut and a coffee mug on a flat surface. This project represents an early-stage modeling and texturing attempt by a beginner, focusing on basic object creation, material application, and workspace familiratiy.
Learnings:
Understanding Blender’s interface and navigation tools (viewport, outliner, properties panel).

Creating primitive shapes (torus for donut, cylinder for mug).

Applying basic materials and colors to objects.

Adjusting object transforms (location, rotation, scale).

Setting up a simple camera view and lighting for scene composition.

Gaining confidence in organizing objects within collections.
